						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śrīpurusa. Year 7: A.D. 732.</hi></p>						

						<p>In <hi rend="italic">Vaṭṭeḻuttu</hi> characters. The inscription is engraved around the images of two individuals holding small daggers and long bows in their hands. <hi rend="italic">Puḷḷis</hi> are marked in some places. Records that two persons namely, Erumaiya Eruvāḍi and Kuṉṟandai Vaḍugaṉ fell while lifting cattle <hi rend="italic">(toṟukkoṇḍa-ñāṉṟu)</hi> when Māṟavoṭṭaiyār was ruling Tāyaṉūr-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
